This package includes the VirtualGL Client application, which enables Intel-based Macintosh computers to receive and re-composite 3D images from a VirtualGL server using the VGL Transport.  It is not necessary to install this package when using VirtualGL with VNC and other X proxies.  The Macintosh X11 application (which is not installed by default but which can be installed from the OS X distribution discs) must be installed prior to using the VirtualGL Client.\
\
Refer to the VirtualGL documentation (a link to which is provided in the Applications folder) for usage information.\
